 <h1><span class=field-wrapper>Smart Cities and Buildings</span>
</h1>
 
 
 </section>
<section id=block-archadvisory-content class=block-archadvisory-content>
 
 
 
 
 
<article id=node-149 data-history-node-id=149 role=article about=/industries/smart-cities class="node-type-general_content_page view-mode-full">
 
 
 
 <div class=view-mode-full>
 <div class="field-wrapper body field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 <p><span>The concept of a smart city is not new, but it is still nascent and the definition remains quite heterogenous. Broadly, a smart city is connected, intelligent and optimized by a municipality to reduce costs, increase safety, attract investment, be sustainable, and enhance livability. To get there will require smart governance, the education of a smart workforce and smart citizens, the digital transformation of assets, and the deployment of sensor networks with ubiquitous multimodal connectivity. </span></p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-hero-background-image field--type-image field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 <img src='data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="1200" height="733"><rect fill-opacity="0"/></svg>' width=1200 height=733 alt="Smart City Connectivity" class="b-lazy b-loaded" typeof=foaf:Image style="background-blend-mode:normal!important;background-clip:content-box!important;background-position:50% 50%!important;background-color:rgba(0,0,0,0)!important;background-image:var(--sf-img-7)!important;background-size:100% 100%!important;background-origin:content-box!important;background-repeat:no-repeat!important">
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="field-node--field-paragraph-bundles field-wrapper field field--name-field-paragraph-bundles field--type-entity-reference-revisions field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class="field-item field__item">
 <section class="paragraph paragraph__two-column paragraph--type--two-columns paragraph--view-mode--default">
 <h2 class=paragraph--title> <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-bundle-title field--type-string field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 Smart Cities Overview
 </div>
 </div>
</h2>
 <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-bundle-content field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 <p><span>Smart cities present tremendous opportunities for industrial IoT vendors, but the technical challenges, vast number of players in this ecosystem, and the fact that it bridges private, public, and consumer realms makes navigating and succeeding in this market a challenge. Cybersecurity, connectivity and working with municipal bureaucracy remain the biggest challenges, but other obstacles include; exponential data volume growth, data cleansing speed, the need to go from cloud to edge architectures, quantifying results, interoperability, and human fears/resistance to transformational change such as Artificial Intelligence.</span></p>
<p>ARC analysts are the experts in all areas of industry, infrastructure, and cities.&nbsp; <span>ARC has identified 12 key smart city application sectors: </span></p>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="row paragraph__two-column--columns">
 <div class="columns small-12 medium-6">
 <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-left-column field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 <ul><li>Smart Amenities</li>
 <li>Smart Building</li>
 <li>Smart Education</li>
 <li>Smart Environment</li>
 <li>Smart Finance</li>
 <li>Smart Governance</li>
</ul>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="columns small-12 medium-6">
 <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-right-column field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 <ul><li>Smart Health</li>
 <li>Smart Manufacturing &amp; Construction</li>
 <li>Smart Public Safety &amp; Security</li>
 <li>Smart Retail &amp; Logistics</li>
 <li>Smart Transportation</li>
 <li>Smart Utilities</li>
</ul>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
</section>
 </div>
 <div class="field-item field__item">
 
<section class="paragraph paragraph__callout paragraph--type--text-and-callout paragraph--view-mode--default">
 <h2 class=paragraph--title> <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-bundle-title field--type-string field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 Smart Buildings Overview
 </div>
 </div>
</h2>
 
 <div class="row callout__right">
 <div class="columns small-12 medium-4 paragraph__callout__right">
 
<div>
 <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-content field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 <p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p style=text-align:center><img alt="Building Automation Services.PNG" data-entity-type data-entity-uuid height=253 width=419 class="b-lazy b-loaded" src=data:image/png;base64,></p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 <div class="columns small-12 medium-8">
 <div class=row>
 <div class="columns medium-10 paragraph__content__wrapper">
 <aside class=paragraph--content>
 <div class="field-wrapper field field--name-field-bundle-content field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__items">
 <div class=field__item>
 <p>Today, building automation has evolved significantly beyond control systems for HVAC and lighting. While the concept of smart buildings has been around for some time now, with the emergence of IoT and a new generation of intelligent edge devices, smart has taken on an entirely new meaning for building automation.</p>
<p>Buildings of all sizes and functions, residential or commercial, are becoming connected smart ecosystems in which systems monitor and maintain much more than climate control and lighting. Intelligent edge devices will do more than just gather point data. They will also aggregate, analyze, and stream data to edge computing where advanced predictive analytic engines will enable new levels of control and security, while significantly improving the overall user experience in the building environment. These new systems will be smarter, self-learning, innovative, and highly sophisticated.</p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </aside>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
 </div>
</section>
 </div>
